node.text: I can’t wait to see these cottages surrounded by fall colours. We are open through the fall and winter and yes, there are still availabilities. 📷 @kyla.something

node.text: Moving Midsummer was quite the ordeal and yet so worth it. We’ve had such good feedback from our guests who love being out in nature while staying within walking distance from local bakeries and restaurants. One of my favourite things about Midsummer is how everyone can picture it as part of a different story (we’ve heard everything from Hansel & Gretel to Twilight). Adding the mountain view in the background became the perfect final touch. Photo @kyla.something

node.text:
We are hearing good things from Lia’s guests so far. I love her too! Thank you for your feedback yesterday. We will take all it to some very intense planning meetings in the next few weeks:) 
📷@kyla.something

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Charmed Family in Crowsnest Pass, Alberta. May be an image of outdoors and tree.

node.text: Lia Cottage is my favourite build of ours. It’s smaller and more humble than some of others but it’s folksy details and soft colour palette make me feel like I’m home. If you get the chance to stay at Lia and spend some time gazing at each feature, you will get a strong sense of the talent and passion of the people we get to work with each day from design to construction. Now that our fourth cottage has been turned over to guests, it’s time for us to focus hard on what’s coming next. We have big plans and expect the resort to be completely transformed by spring. Our immediate goal is to get three more cottages in this glade as soon as possible, one more elf house and two more larger builds with Rapunzel-level wow-factor. We have some ideas forming but would love to hear your thoughts! What would you love to see our next builds be? 📸 @kyla.something

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Charmed Family in Crowsnest Pass, Alberta. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: Our first official Lia post is brought to you by @iiokitchen and their beautiful, buttercream Fun Fridge. Lia Cottage is our fourth cottage and my favourite build we’ve ever done. She is intricate yet delicate, more folksy than fancy and needed the perfect vintage fridge to match her aesthetic. This smaller-sized fridge fit perfectly in the kitchenette. Check out more size and colour options at the link in our bio. #ad

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Charmed Family in Crowsnest Pass, Alberta with @etsy, @olliella, @piperclassics, @smallable_store, and @maisontess. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: I thought I should give everyone a heads up that summer 2022 is booking up and much faster than we expected. The resort will be much bigger by then so don’t fret if you miss out on your current favourite cottage. Rapunzel was so popular that we will be adding 2 more cottages that (we think) will excite her fans just as much! We are also adding 1 more elf house before fall. By next spring, we will be expanding up into the mountain and adding a few more surprises(including an easier booking system). This whole summer has been the greatest adventure and we are so grateful you have joined us on it. Photo @kyla.something

node.text: Rapunzel searched high and low for the perfect fairytale fridge to go with her soft mauve cabinet. She was delighted to team up with @iiokitchen to incorporate their Fun Fridge into her storybook cottage. It is the perfect compact size for her quaint space and even has a freezer for ice cream on hot summer days. Rapunzel chose Buttercream but they have a beautiful selection of colours to choose from. Shop at the link in our bio and we’ll show you how it looks in Lia Cottage so so soon!
